So I've ended up with abstract class such as this which allow you to pass return types, in this case it goes 3 or 4 deep before I create a concrete class. It seems to work but feels a bit clunky when I assigning multiple TypeVar's.

Just looking for opinions :)

`
T = TypeVar("T", bound=PlcResponse)


class PlcRequest(Generic[T], ABC):
    """
    Base type for all messages sent from the plc4x system to a connected plc.
    """

    @abstractmethod
    def execute(self) -> Future[T]:
        pass


U = TypeVar("U", bound=PlcFieldResponse)


class PlcFieldRequest(PlcRequest[U]):
    def __init__(self, fields: list[PlcField] = []):
        self.fields = fields

    @abstractmethod
    def execute(self) -> Future[U]:
        pass

    @property
    def field_names(self):
        return [field.name for field in self.fields]
`
